node.text:
Here at New Belgium, we love two things: beer & vessels for drinking beer. That’s why we’re so excited about our 2021 Artist Series globe glasses from renowned artists Hyland Mather and Cody Hudson. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
These glasses are extra special because it’s our 30th anniversary—and to be honest—we wanted to celebrate with a lil’ glassware birthday gift. It’s our party & we’ll drink if we want to! ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
All jokes aside, Hyland and Cody had such wonderful things to say about their process & design inspiration—and we’re stoked to share their thoughts & glasses with you. Link in bio to purchase them online, or swing by one of our LC's to pick them up.⁠⁠
#newbelgium #artistseries #craftbeer

node.text:
Although beer will be the least of our worries in a full-on climate crisis, we love beer, and we don't want to imagine a world where it tastes like this.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Curious to try it yourself? There's a limited number to order via our link in bio or swing by to pick up a 4-pack at our Asheville or Fort Collins taprooms (now open!).⁠⁠
#newbelgium #thenbeer #forceforgood

node.text:
This Earth Day, we think it’s about time we give big business a last call. 70% of fortune‐500 companies don't have a meaningful plan to address climate change by 2030, and we need these corporations to join us in using their power and influence as a force for good. Because the future of beer could taste pretty bad, and nobody wants that to happen. Hit our link in bio to ask them to commit to climate action now.⁠⁠
#newbelgium #torchedearth #thenbeer #forceforgood

How it started is the stuff of urban legend, but New Belgium is known for the long-standing tradition of gifting employees with a limited edition bike on their one-year anniversary. When it came to building our 30th-anniversary version, we knew a project this special meant calling on the best of the best. @brooklynbikeco and @joshua_ariza of @chompbrand came together and designed a custom bike that embodies our core values and looks damn good doing it, too. Go behind the scenes with the folks responsible for this year’s epic ride. #newbelgium #newbelgium30 #craftbeer⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Want a chance to win one of these bad boys for yourself? Hit our link in bio and enter now!⁠⁠

Need a spoonful of inspiration to help fight the Sunday scaries? We’ve got just the remedy. 

We sat down with our founder Kim Jordan and discussed the history of New Belgium and her commitment to making beer a force for good in the world. Maybe we’re a little biased, but it’s a pretty wonderful story - and we’re so excited to share it with you.
#newbelgium #craftbeer #forceforgood

node.text:
BFFs aka Beer friends forever. Here’s a lil’ fun fact for you: The Town Pump was the first place to have Fat Tire on draft. That means that 30 years ago (almost to the day) the very first draft Fat Tire was poured. It’s pretty wild to reflect on, especially because craft beer and Fort Collins have changed so much since then. But one thing remains the same—the Town Pump, with its decades of bumper stickers, rich wood walls, and an endless supply of Fat Tire.

Continue the journey and head to our link in bio to see the newly unveiled Fat Tire website!

There’s nothing like cracking open a cold one while diving into a good book. The top pick on our summer reading list? “All We Can Save: Truth, Courage and Solutions for the Climate Crisis.” The book represents a wide range of essays and creative works by over 50 women involved in climate change activism, science, and policy. Because brewing world-class beer requires the best ingredients, and climate change is an immediate threat to them. It’s that simple.

We’re celebrating the new paperback edition of this bestselling anthology tomorrow by joining co-editors @ayanaeliza and @drkwilkinson, plus a slate of special guests, and you should too! RSVP via our link in bio.
#newbelgium #forceforgood

Do they make a Best for the Environment™ mug? Because if so, we’d have it on our desk today. We’re so proud to be named a Best for the Environment B Corp of 2021, with a score in the top 10%. This specific impact area takes into account the effect of a business’s everyday footprint including energy usage, materials, facilities, supply chain, and more. Last year, Fat Tire became America’s first carbon neutral certified beer, and we’re not stopping there. We are committed to all our beers being carbon neutral by 2030. We push forward solutions to the biggest environmental challenges of our time because we can't brew world-class beer without a healthy planet.

Cheers to all the inspiring companies making the list today, and helping us pave the way for business as a force for good. Head to our link in bio to see our full impact report!
#newbelgium #forceforgood #bftw2021

Oh, Hi! 👋 Meet the enchanted result of our liquid partnership with Hard Kombucha makers @FlyingEmbersBrew. With equal parts kombucha and golden sour as the base, we added Ojai, California pixie tangerines and Colorado prairie sage to brew a sessionable sour. When you close your eyes and take a sip, it’s like having the windows rolled down on a road trip from Ojai to Fort Collins. 

In addition to our love for all things funky and fermented, we partnered on this brew to benefit wildfire and disaster relief in our home states of Colorado and California. Together we’ll be donating $10,000 to their nonprofit organization, the Embers Foundation, in support of first responders and the communities they serve. 

Available now for purchase at select retailers in Colorado and Southern California, along with direct shipping to select states, and in our Fort Collins, Asheville, & SF Liquid Centers. Hit the link in bio to grab a 6-pack while they last. Don’t forget to say oh, hi! 

#newbelgium #flyingembers #craftbeer #forceforgood

New Belgium has been brewing world-class beer over the last 30 years, but our award-winning sour program and Carbon Neutral @fattire Ale wouldn’t be here today without our humble beginning. 

The year? 1988. The country? Belgium. The preferred method of transportation? Bike. Our co-founder, Jeff, kept this journal while biking from brewery to brewery across the beautiful, beer-filled country. He documented as much about brewing Belgian style beer as he possibly could in a single spiral-bound notebook, and brought the experience, knowledge and creativity found in Belgian beer home to Fort Collins. With it, he began brewing what would become the world-class beers at the very heart of New Belgium today.

That initial trip turned into a long-standing tradition: as a 5-year perk, employees are sent on an all-expenses-paid trip to Belgium. It’s the perfect opportunity for our coworkers to connect with our roots as a brewery and gain a deeper understanding of Belgian beer history and culture. It’s also one of the many reasons we've landed on Outside Magazine’s “Best Places to Work” since 2010. Whether we're working in accounting, the warehouse, or pouring your beers, over 700 coworkers have been a driving force behind New Belgium's positive impacts in the community. Ultimately, we know rewarding that hard work, and having a helluva lot of fun, is good for business.
#newbelgium #craftbeer #forceforgood #humanpowered
